# No Barrel Files

## Description
Avoid using barrel files (index.ts) for re-exporting modules. Import directly from specific files instead.

## Examples
✅ Valid:
```typescript
// Import directly from the specific file
import { UserService } from './api/user-service.ts';
import { DatabaseConfig } from './config/database-config.ts';
```

❌ Invalid:
```typescript
// Don't use barrel files
import { UserService } from './api';
import { DatabaseConfig } from './config';
```

## Rationale
Avoiding barrel files:
1. Makes dependencies more explicit and traceable
2. Improves build performance by enabling better tree-shaking
3. Reduces the risk of circular dependencies
4. Makes the codebase more maintainable

## Implementation
When importing modules:
1. Always import directly from the specific file
2. Use the full relative path to the file
3. Include the file extension (.ts)
4. Avoid creating index.ts files for re-exporting
